==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[excoriare]]'' "to flay"; ''[[ex-]]'' "off" + ''[[corium]]'' "skin"

=== Transitive Verb ===
'''excoriate'''
# to wear off the [[skin]] of; to [[chafe]]
# to strongly [[renounce]] or [[censure]]

==== Synonyms ====
*[[abrade]] (1)
*[[chafe]] (1)
*[[flay]] (1)
*[[condemn]] (2)
*[[denounce]] (2)
*[[reprobate]] (2)


=== Noun ===
'''excoriator'''
# one who excoriates

'''excoriation'''
# the act of excoriating
# the results of such acts